+# Solution: Cosmos support for top-level Any()
+
+## Root Cause
+
+Cosmos DB does not support uncorrelated subqueries. The existing translation for top-level `Any()` over a root entity query generated:
+
+```sql
+SELECT VALUE EXISTS (
+    SELECT 1
+    FROM root c
+    WHERE (c["Discriminator"] = "Customer"))
+```
+
+`EXISTS(SELECT ... FROM root c ...)` is an uncorrelated subquery at the outermost level, which Cosmos rejects with a `BadRequest` error. This affected `Any()`, `Any(predicate)`, `Contains()`, and other operators that internally delegate to `Any`.
+
+## Change Description
+
+In `CosmosQueryableMethodTranslatingExpressionVisitor.TranslateAny`, added a special path for top-level root-entity queries (`!_subquery && subquery.Sources is [{ WithIn: false }, ..]`):
+
+Instead of wrapping in `EXISTS(subquery)`, the method now:
+1. Applies `LIMIT 1` to the existing `SelectExpression` (fails gracefully if a limit is already present from a prior `Take`)
+2. Clears orderings (irrelevant for existence check)
+3. Replaces the projection mapping with `SqlConstantExpression(true)`
+4. Returns `SingleOrDefault` cardinality — if Cosmos returns one row (`[true]`), the result is `true`; if it returns no rows (`[]`), `SingleOrDefault<bool>` returns `false` (the default)
+
+Generated SQL (e.g. for `Set<Customer>().OrderBy(...).ThenBy(...).Any()`):
+
+```sql
+SELECT VALUE true
+FROM root c
+OFFSET 0 LIMIT 1
+```
+
+When a prior `Take` has already set a limit, `TryApplyLimit` cannot stack another limit (no subquery pushdown in Cosmos), so the method returns `null` (translation failure). This is better than the previous behavior of generating invalid SQL that throws at runtime.
+
+## Files Edited
+
+- `src/EFCore.Cosmos/Query/Internal/CosmosQueryableMethodTranslatingExpressionVisitor.cs` — Core fix in `TranslateAny`
+- `test/EFCore.Cosmos.FunctionalTests/Query/NorthwindMiscellaneousQueryCosmosTest.cs` — Updated `Any_simple`, `Any_predicate`, `OrderBy_ThenBy_Any` (now expect success + correct SQL), `Skip_Take_Any` (now expects translation failure instead of runtime CosmosException)
+- `test/EFCore.Cosmos.FunctionalTests/Query/NorthwindAggregateOperatorsQueryCosmosTest.cs` — Updated `Contains_top_level`, `Contains_over_entityType_with_null_should_rewrite_to_false` (now expect success + correct SQL)
+
+## Precedent Usage
+
+**Query 1:** `"Cosmos Any top-level EXISTS LIMIT 1 uncorrelated subquery"` — returned PR #37603 (score 0.51, below threshold). The PR added the `IsRootEntityQuery` helper (`subquery.Sources is [{ WithIn: false }, ..]`) to detect root entity queries in `TranslateSetOperation`. I reused the same detection pattern in `TranslateAny`.
+
+**Query 2:** `"top level Any boolean OFFSET LIMIT true projection"` — returned only below-threshold results. Not useful.
+
+**Query 3:** `"CosmosQueryableMethodTranslatingExpressionVisitor root entity query non-correlated subquery detection"` — again returned PR #37603 as the top result. Confirmed the `IsRootEntityQuery` pattern and the `SourceExpression.WithIn` field as the discriminator between root collection queries and array-join sources.
